> This isn't your normal salad. Bursting with fresh veg which have been combined with the sharp flavour of capers and a kick of heat from the Chilli Flakes. Paired with fresh Butternut Squash and creamy Feta cheese, this is one of our favourite recipes and we're pretty sure it's about to become yours too.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Put the @diced butternut squash{300%g} on a large lined #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Mix well, arrange in a single layer on the tray, then pop on the top shelf of your oven to roast until tender and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(thinly sliced). Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1}(halved and cored) and slice into thin strips. Heat a splash of oil in large #frying pan{} over medium-low heat. Add the onion, pepper and a pinch of @chilli flakes{1%pinch}. Gently cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion and pepper are really soft, ~{15-20%minutes}.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @premium tomato mix{125%g}(halved). Pick the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} and @thyme{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks (keeping them separate!) and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Tear the @ciabatta{1} into small, bite-sized pieces and drain the @capers{15%g} in a #sieve{}. Zest then halve the @lemon{1/2}(zested and halved).

When the squash has been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, add the tomatoes and garlic to the tray with another drizzle of oil if you need it. Gently mix and return to the oven for the remainder of the cooking time. Meanwhile, make the dressing by combining the @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @?sugar{1/2%tsp}, lemon zest and juice from the lemon in a #mixing bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper, mix well and set aside.

Put the ciabatta on another lined baking tray with a drizzle of oil, the thyme leaves and a good pinch of salt. Toss together well then spread out and place the tray on the middle shelf of your oven to toast until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Give the tray a shake halfway through cooking.

Stir the capers into the pan with the onion and pepper then tip them all into the #bowl{} with the dressing. Remove the roasted veggies and croutons from the oven, add to the bowl and gently mix. Let the bowl sit for a couple of minutes (to let the bread absorb the flavours!) then mix in the @wild rocket{40%g} and parsley. Divide between plates and top with the @feta cheese{100%g}(crumbled). Enjoy!